   "source": [
    "Data visualization:\n",
    "It is the process of representing data in a graphical or visual format such as charts,graphs, maps,etc so that people can easily understand patterns, trends and insights.\n",
    "\n",
    "Advantage:\n",
    "    - makes data easy to understand\n",
    "    - helps in quick decision making\n",
    "    - identifies patterns and trends\n",
    "    - detects outliers or errors\n",
    "    - improves communication of insights\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "a42254e7-ed47-4366-8c81-cdf47d4d48f8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Univariate Analysis:\n",
    "It means analyzing only one vaariable at a time.To check the quality of the data.\n",
    "\n",
    "Purpose:\n",
    "    -understand distribution\n",
    "    -find patterns\n",
    "    -detect outliers\n",
    "    -ex. histogram , Box plot , KDE plot , violin plot \n",
    "Ex. analyze salary distribution in a company \n",
    "    :are most employees low paid or high paid"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "5b88f538-8207-4091-b34b-da6bc72a6375",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Bivariate Analysis:\n",
    "It means analyzing the relation between two variables.\n",
    "\n",
    "Purpose:\n",
    "    -understand relationship\n",
    "    -identify correlation\n",
    "    -dompare variables\n",
    "    -ex. scatter plot , bar plot , line plot \n",
    "Ex. analyze advertising spend vs sales \n",
    "    :does increasing ads increase sales"
   ]
  },
